The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | One killed, four injured in mishaps
                                                                                                               One killed, four injured in mishaps
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	A man died and four persons were injured in three mishaps in the city on Thursday night and Friday. A 65-year-old unidentified pedestrian was knocked down by a state bus at the Amherst Street-Surya Sen Street crossing on Friday. He was declared dead at NRS hospital. On Thursday, the driver and help of a goods vehicle were injured after it rammed into a stationary oil tanker on Kidderpore Road. Both were admitted to SSKM Hospital. An army vehicle hit a motorcycle on Alipore Road on Thursday night injuring Madan Pandey and pillion rider Kripasindhu Pandey, both in their 50s. They were admitted to Kothari Hospital.                                                                                                                                                                           
